### Play4Change — Admin Topic Creation Flow
### JetBrains HTTP Client (.http)
###
### Flow order:
###   0. Promote user to ADMIN (SQL — one-time setup)
###   1. Admin login via magic link (same as auth.http)
###   2. Create topic from URL   → topic starts in GENERATING status
###   3. Create topic from PDF   → multipart upload
###   4. Poll topic status       → wait for ACTIVE (or FAILED if no Mistral key)
###   5. List all topics
###   6. Regenerate tasks from stored content
###
### NOTE: There is no task-template edit endpoint in the current codebase.
###       (VERIFY: PUT /admin/topics/{id}/tasks/{taskId} does not exist —
###        check TopicController.kt and TopicUseCase.kt if this has been added.)

@baseUrl = http://localhost:8080

# Fill in after admin login (step 1):
@adminToken = <paste admin accessToken here>

# Fill in after topic creation (step 2 or 3):
@topicId = <paste topic id here>

###############################################################################

### 0. Promote a user to ADMIN role (one-time DB setup — no seed endpoint exists)
#
# After the user has logged in at least once via magic link (which creates the
# users row), run this SQL against the PostgreSQL container:
#
#   docker exec -it play4change-postgres psql -U play4change -d play4change -c \
#     "UPDATE users SET role = 'ADMIN' WHERE email = 'admin@ example.com';"
#
# Verify:
#   docker exec -it play4change-postgres psql -U play4change -d play4change -c \
#     "SELECT id, email, role FROM users WHERE email = 'admin@ example.com';"
#
# The user must then log out and log back in — the role is embedded in the JWT
# at issue time via TokenService. Existing tokens are NOT retroactively upgraded.

###############################################################################

### 1a. Request admin magic link
POST {{baseUrl}}/auth/magic-link
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "admin@example.com"
}

###############################################################################

### 1b. Verify magic link → get admin JWT
# Paste the token from server logs:
#   docker logs play4change-server --follow 2>&1 | grep -A3 "MAGIC LINK"
# The response accessToken will carry role=ADMIN in the JWT claims.
# Paste it into @ adminToken above.
GET {{baseUrl}}/auth/verify?token=<paste-token-from-logs>
Accept: application/json

###############################################################################

### 2. Create topic from URL
# The server fetches and extracts the page content, then kicks off async AI
# task generation. The topic is created immediately with status=GENERATING.
# Poll GET /admin/topics/{id} until status=ACTIVE (or FAILED).
#
# audienceLevel values: BEGINNER | INTERMEDIATE | ADVANCED
# language: BCP-47 tag, e.g. "en", "pt"
# expiresAt: ISO-8601 with offset, e.g. "2026-12-31T23:59:59Z"
# taskCount: number of daily tasks to generate (one per day)
# subscriptionWindowDays: how many days users can enrol after topic creation
#
# Response: 201 Created — TopicResponse
POST {{baseUrl}}/admin/topics
Content-Type: application/json
Authorization: Bearer {{adminToken}}

{
  "title": "Introduction to Circular Economy",
  "description": "Learn the core principles of circular economy and sustainable resource use.",
  "url": "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Circular_economy",
  "taskCount": 7,
  "subscriptionWindowDays": 14,
  "audienceLevel": "BEGINNER",
  "language": "en",
  "expiresAt": "2026-12-31T23:59:59Z"
}

###############################################################################

### 3. Create topic from PDF (multipart/form-data)
#
# Place a real PDF at demo/sample-topic.pdf before running this request.
# The server stores the PDF in MinIO, extracts text via PDFBox, then triggers
# async AI generation exactly as the URL flow does.
#
# IMPORTANT: If MISTRAL_API_KEY is not set, NoOpTaskGenerationAdapter runs
# instead of LangChain4jTaskGenerationAdapter. The topic will transition to
# ACTIVE immediately with placeholder/empty tasks — no real generation occurs.
# Set MISTRAL_API_KEY in your .env file for real generation.
#
# @RequestParam fields (form fields, NOT JSON):
#   title, description, taskCount, subscriptionWindowDays,
#   audienceLevel, language, expiresAt
# @RequestPart field name: file
#
# Response: 201 Created — TopicResponse
POST {{baseUrl}}/admin/topics/pdf
Authorization: Bearer {{adminToken}}
Content-Type: multipart/form-data; boundary=DemoBoundary

--DemoBoundary
Content-Disposition: form-data; name="title"

Sustainability in Urban Planning
--DemoBoundary
Content-Disposition: form-data; name="description"

A challenge on integrating green infrastructure and sustainable design in cities.
--DemoBoundary
Content-Disposition: form-data; name="taskCount"

5
--DemoBoundary
Content-Disposition: form-data; name="subscriptionWindowDays"

10
--DemoBoundary
Content-Disposition: form-data; name="audienceLevel"

INTERMEDIATE
--DemoBoundary
Content-Disposition: form-data; name="language"

en
--DemoBoundary
Content-Disposition: form-data; name="expiresAt"

2026-12-31T23:59:59Z
--DemoBoundary
Content-Disposition: form-data; name="file"; filename="sample-topic.pdf"
Content-Type: application/pdf

< ./sample-topic.pdf
--DemoBoundary--

###############################################################################

### 4. Poll topic status
# Copy the topic id from the 201 response into @ topicId above.
# Poll until "status" is "ACTIVE".
# If MISTRAL_API_KEY is not set → status will be "ACTIVE" instantly (NoOp adapter).
# If MISTRAL_API_KEY is set → status transitions DRAFT → GENERATING → ACTIVE
#                             (AI call takes up to 60 s; circuit breaker retries 3×).
# If all AI retries fail  → status = "FAILED" (check server logs for cause).
#
# Response: 200 OK — TopicResponse
GET {{baseUrl}}/admin/topics/{{topicId}}
Authorization: Bearer {{adminToken}}
Accept: application/json

###############################################################################

### 5. List all topics (optional status filter)
# status query param values: DRAFT | GENERATING | ACTIVE | EXPIRED | FAILED
# Omit status to list all.
#
# Response: 200 OK — List<TopicResponse>
GET {{baseUrl}}/admin/topics?status=ACTIVE
Authorization: Bearer {{adminToken}}
Accept: application/json

###############################################################################

### 5b. List all topics (no filter)
GET {{baseUrl}}/admin/topics
Authorization: Bearer {{adminToken}}
Accept: application/json

###############################################################################

### 6. Regenerate tasks from stored content
# Triggers a fresh async AI generation run using the raw_extracted_text already
# stored in the database (no re-upload or re-fetch needed).
# Sets topic status back to GENERATING; transitions to ACTIVE or FAILED on completion.
# Requires MISTRAL_API_KEY to be set for real output.
#
# Response: 200 OK — TopicResponse (status = GENERATING)
POST {{baseUrl}}/admin/topics/{{topicId}}/regenerate
Authorization: Bearer {{adminToken}}
Content-Type: application/json

